Operatives of Delta State Police Command, yesterday, invaded a baby factory in Okpanam community,  Oshimili North Local Council of the state and arrested 29- year-old Aruna Sulieman and one Promise Ejogu, suspected to be operators of the centre.  “And following the information, police joint team of the State Anti-Cult (SACU), Ibusa Division and local vigilantes swung into action, and raided their hideout, where 25 male suspects were arrested.
 
“Recovered from them are three Aye confraternity regalias, one military vest,  a pair of Aye confraternity stockings,  three cut-to-size locally made guns, four live cartridges,  a gallon of substances suspected to be liquid hard drugs, four vehicles, and four motorcycles”. ALSO, the Area Command, Asaba, has arrested 10 suspected cultists and recovered one fabricated AK47 rifle, charms, fake Vigilante Identity card  and AC&DC Black Axe confraternity regalia. “ The police received intelligence reports on some suspected cultists hibernating somewhere in Mile 5, a boundary between Oshimili North and Oshimili South Local Councils, who were planning to attack innocent citizens in the area.
 
“The Area Commander alerted the Commissioner of Police, Ari Muhammed Ali, who ordered a massive raid in the area and a combined team comprising of raiders squad, operatives from GRA Division and Area Command,  Asaba, led by the Area Crime officer, Kufre Udofia, stormed the hideout and arrested them,” Edafe added. 